<section class="sec reveal" id="qec-tldr" style="padding-top:8px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">QuickBooks error codes, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="tldr-prose speakable"><p id="qec-tldr-body">QuickBooks errors fall into <strong>six recognizable families</strong>: <strong>H-series</strong> (H101, H202, H505 &mdash; multi-user and network connectivity), <strong>6000-series</strong> (6000-77, 6000-301, 6189, 6190 &mdash; file access and integrity), <strong>PS-series</strong> (PS032, PS036, PS038 &mdash; payroll subscription and tax tables), <strong>3000- and 80000-series</strong> (3371, 80070057 &mdash; license validation and file path), <strong>15000-series</strong> (15215, 15240 &mdash; payroll updates and maintenance), and <strong>unrecoverable / C-series</strong> (file corruption and critical faults). The codes in this reference apply almost entirely to <strong>QuickBooks Desktop, Premier, Mac, and Enterprise</strong>; <a href="/quickbooks/online/">QuickBooks Online</a> uses descriptive text messages rather than numbered codes. The honest read: many first-occurrence errors resolve with documented self-fix steps (QuickBooks Tool Hub, firewall checks, configuration adjustments) &mdash; the dedicated page for each code walks you through them. But errors that <strong>recur, cluster, involve file corruption, or block critical work</strong> typically require a <a href="/quickbooks/cleanup/">Certified ProAdvisor&rsquo;s file repair</a>, scoped as fixed-fee work after a 30-minute diagnostic. Independent ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qec-families" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The six error families</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Find your error&rsquo;s family.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Most QuickBooks errors fall into one of these six families. Identify your code&rsquo;s family, then scan the specific codes below. If your error isn&rsquo;t resolving, a <a href="/contact/?intent=qb-error">ProAdvisor diagnostic</a> identifies the real cause.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for f in families %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ f.codes }}</span><h3>{{ f.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ f.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qec-h-series">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">H-series</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Multi-user mode &amp; network errors.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">H-series errors share a root: QuickBooks is configured for multi-user but a workstation can&rsquo;t reach the company file on the host. The specific code narrows where in that chain the problem is.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for c in hSeries %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{% if c.href %}<a href="{{ c.href }}">{{ c.name | safe }}</a>{% else %}{{ c.name | safe }}{% endif %}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ c.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qec-6000-series" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">6000-series</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">File access &amp; integrity errors.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:72ch;">6000-series errors involve the company file itself &mdash; whether QuickBooks can open it, whether it&rsquo;s locked, whether it&rsquo;s damaged, or whether permissions are correct. <a href="/quickbooks/help/error-codes/error-6000-series/">The complete 6000-series overview</a> covers every variant.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for c in sixThousand %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{% if c.href %}<a href="{{ c.href }}">{{ c.name | safe }}</a>{% else %}{{ c.name | safe }}{% endif %}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ c.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

