<section class="sec reveal" id="qec-operator">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Who diagnoses your error</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Certified ProAdvisors who&rsquo;ve seen this code before.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Error codes look intimidating because they&rsquo;re cryptic by design &mdash; QuickBooks doesn&rsquo;t explain what H202 or PS038 actually means. But every error in this reference has been resolved many times over by Certified ProAdvisors. The diagnostic isn&rsquo;t guesswork; it&rsquo;s pattern recognition &mdash; matching the code, its context, and the file&rsquo;s state against errors already solved.</p>
      <p>Every TechBrot operator holds active Certified ProAdvisor credentials across Desktop, Enterprise, Online (Level 2), and Payroll, verifiable on Intuit&rsquo;s public ProAdvisor directory. We earn nothing from your QuickBooks subscription &mdash; so the recommendation you get is what fixes your error, not what bills more. You can <a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/">meet the ProAdvisor team</a> or read our <a href="/trust/">trust &amp; methodology standards</a>. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row" style="margin-top:22px;">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
